A pastor is among four suspects who have been arrested over the killing of a police reservist in Kerio Valley near Kabetwa on Saturday.The four were arrested as they sought treatment at the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital in Eldoret.The church where the pastor works is along the Pokot-Marakwet border. Police said the four travelled from Tiaty to Eldoret a day after the reservist was killed in a gunfight between bandits and the police.